responded: Now I can see the issue! At line 4330, `EX(call)` is modified to `call->prev_execute_data`, and at line 4332, `call` is updated to `EX(call)`. However, at line 4315, the code is calling `zend_vm_stack_free_args(EX(call))` instead of `zend_vm_stack_free_args(call)`. 

This means that `EX(call)` might not be the same as the local `call` variable at line 4315, and could potentially be corrupted or invalid. The fix should be to use the local `call` variable instead of `EX(call)`.

Let me create the patch:

args.patch:
diff --git a/Zend/zend_execute.c b/Zend/zend_execute.c
index 0df529203c1..b0e29aec6fe 100644
--- a/Zend/zend_execute.c
+++ b/Zend/zend_execute.c
@@ -4312,7 +4312,7 @@ static void cleanup_unfinished_calls(zend_execute_data *execute_data, uint32_t o
 				} while (!do_exit);
 			}

